==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swinger
<hw>Swin"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
swinges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything very large, forcible, or astonishing.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Herrick.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 3. [Colloq.] <def>A person who engages frequently in lively and
fashionable pursuits, such as attending night clubs or discos.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> 4. <def>A person who engages freely in sexual intercourse.</def>
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swingle</ent>⟦br⟧
